<p>I'm build a plugin for myself, and Trying to using Blueimp File Upload plugin to upload image on frontend. where user visitor can upload the image to the web.</p>  <p>I have following form :</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form id="form"&gt;     &lt;input type="file" name="files[]" id="image-upload-1" /&gt;     &lt;input type="file" name="files[]" id="image-upload-2" /&gt;     &lt;input type="file" name="files[]" id="image-upload-3" /&gt;     &lt;input type="submit" name="submit" value="submit" /&gt; &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I have code to upload image when click submit :</p>  <pre><code>$(document).ready(function () {         var sendData= true;         $('#image-upload-1, #image-upload-2, #image-upload-3').fileupload({             url: params.ajax_url,             dataType : 'json',             autoUpload : false,             add : function(e,data){                 $('#form input[type="submit"]').on("click",function(){                     if(sendData){                         data.formData = {action: "order_online_upload", _wpnonce: params._wpnonce};                         sendData = false;                     }                      data.submit();                 });             },             done: function(e,data){                 sendData = true;             }         }) }); </code></pre>  <p><strong>What I want is</strong></p>  <p>how to upload image of those input files image with blueimp ? I have done with upload, but I only can upload just 1 file from <code>image-upload-1</code></p>